# Little Fighter Translation Rules

## Font
Always use **Px437 IBM VGA 8x14** (`~/Library/Fonts/Px437_IBM_VGA_8x14.ttf`) at 16pt for all GRH text translations. Do NOT use Perfect DOS VGA 437.

## GRH Workflow
- Always start from the git original when making changes: `git show HEAD:SYS/<file>.GRH`
- Preserve the original `debug/<name>.png` — never overwrite it
- Write translated previews to `debug/<name>_translated.png`
- Only clear pixels matching the text color index being replaced — don't damage surrounding graphics
- Use the correct background palette index for each image region when clearing text

## Palette
- PAL file at `SYS/PAL` — 256 colors, VGA 6-bit (multiply by 4 for 8-bit RGB)
- Green text: palette index 15 `(0, 252, 0)`
- Blue background: palette index 0 `(0, 0, 252)` or indices 107/108/109 depending on image
- Pink/lavender outline: palette index 8 `(200, 200, 252)`
- Dark table background: palette index 98 `(0, 88, 24)` or index 34 `(108, 0, 0)`

## GRH Format
- Bytes 0-1: width (big-endian uint16)
- Bytes 2-3: height (big-endian uint16)
- Bytes 4-299: zero padding
- Bytes 300+: raw 8-bit pixel data (1 byte per pixel, palette indexed)
